Paper: hep-th/9510190

Date: 1995-10-25

Title: Supergravity solitons and non-perturbative superstrings

Comments: Latex 8pp. To appear in Procs. of 1995 Trieste Spring Superstring

School and WorkshopJournal-ref: Nucl.Phys.Proc.Suppl. 45BC (1996) 188-195

A review is given of the implications of supersymmetric black holes for thenon-perturbative formulation of toroidally compactified superstrings, withparticular emphasis on symmetry enhancement at special vacua and S-duality ofthe heterotic string.